4\n}}\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1880= 91\n|1900= 332\n|1910= 428\n|1920= 754\n|1930= 860\n|1940= 791\n|1950= 1061\n|1960= 1352\n|1970= 1825\n|1980= 2450\n|1990= 3730\n|2000= 6425\n|2010= 9288\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=9452\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=August 16, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\n\n===2010 census===\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name =\"wwwcensusgov\">{{cite web|title=U.S. Census website|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2013-01-25}}</ref> of 2010, there were 9,288 people, 3,107 households, and 2,453 families residing in the city. The [[population density]] was {{convert|2254.4|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|1}}. There were 3,225 housing units at an average density of {{convert|782.8|/sqmi|/km2|1}}. The racial makeup of the town was 92.1% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2.4% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.2% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 2.2% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.9% from [[Race (U.S. Census)|other races]], and 2.1% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 4.7% of the population.\n\nThere were 3,107 households of which 50.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 65.2% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 9.3% had a female householder with no husband present, 4.4% had a male householder with no wife present, and 21.0% were non-families. 16.7% of all households were made up of individuals and 7.7% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.97 and the average family size was 3.36.\n\nThe median age in the city was 36.1 years. 32% of residents were under the age of 18; 6.1% were between the ages of 18 and 24; 28.2% were from 25 to 44; 25.4% were from 45 to 64; and 8.3% were 65 years of age or older. The gender makeup of the town was 48.5% male and 51.5% female.\n\n===2000 census===\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 6,425 people, 2,123 households, and 1,717 families residing in the city. The [[population density]] was 1,678.5 people per square mile (647.7/km\u00b2). There were 2,179 housing units at an average density of 569.3 per square mile (219.7/km\u00b2). The racial makeup of the town was 94.71% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 2.58% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.23% [[Native American (U.S. Census)|Native American]], 0.87% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.25% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 1.35% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 1.34% of the population. 24% of Mount Airy's residents were [[German Americans|German]], 19% [[Irish Americans|Irish]], 12% [[English Americans|English]], 7% [[Italian Americans|Italian]], 4% [[Scottish Americans|Scottish]], 3% [[French Americans|French]], 3% [[African Americans|Black or African-American]], 2% [[Dutch Americans|Dutch]], 2% [[Polish Americans|Polish]] and 2% [[Welsh Americans|Welsh]]. People of [[Scotch-Irish Americans|Scotch-Irish]], [[British Americans|British]], [[Ukrainian Americans|Ukrainian]], [[Yugoslav Americans|Yugoslavian]], [[Russian Americans|Russian]], [[French Canadian Americans|French-Canadian]], [[Czech Americans|Czech]], [[Swedish Americans|Swedish]] and [[Norwegian Americans|Norwegian]] descent each comprised 1% of the population.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.epodunk.com/cgi-bin/genealogyInfo.php?locIndex=2695 |title=Mount Airy, MD, Ancestry & Family History |publisher=Epodunk.com |accessdate=2017-07-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151008114324/http://www.epodunk.com/cgi-bin/genealogyInfo.php?locIndex=2695 |archive-date=2015-10-08 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nThere were 2,123 households out of which 51.4% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 69.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 8.5% had a female householder with no husband present, and 19.1% were non-families. 14.9% of all households were made up of individuals and 5.2% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 3.02 and the average family size was 3.37.\n\nIn the city the population was spread out with 34.4% under the age of 18, 5.4% from 18 to 24, 37.1% from 25 to 44, 16.9% from 45 to 64, and 6.2% who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 33 years. For every 100 females there were 98.5 males. For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 93.2 males.\n\nThe median income for a household in the city was $66,967, and the median income for a family was $76,214. Males had a median income of $52,177 versus $35,054 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $25,380. About 2.0% of families and 3.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 4.4% of those under age 18 and 1.8% of those age 65 or over.\n\n==Education==\nMount Airy is home to three elementary schools and one middle school. The first, Mount Airy Elementary, was built and occupied in 1935. In the mid-1980s, the school received major renovations both inside and out. The school has a natural-gas-fired heating system, school-wide air conditioning, and Internet access from the classrooms and computer lab.<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.carrollk12.org/mae/history/default.asp| title=Picture History| work=Mt. Airy Elementary School| publisher=Carroll County Public Schools| accessdate=May 27, 2016}}</ref>\n\nParr's Ridge Elementary School was built in 2005 due to serious overcrowding at Mount Airy Elementary. Parr's Ridge enrolls students from kindergarten through Grade 2, while Mount Airy Elementary School enrolls students in grades 3\u20135. Mount Airy Middle School is located next to Mount Airy Elementary. Twin Ridge Elementary School is located on the western edge of Mount Airy and unlike the other schools is run by Frederick County Public Schools.\n\nMount Airy Middle School was originally constructed in 1958 and served as a high school until 1967, then served as a middle school until 2013. Construction began on a new middle school in June 2011 and was opened for the school year starting in the fall of 2013. The old middle school building was demolished in the same year.\n\nStudents in grades 9 through 12 living in the Frederick County portion of Mount Airy attend [[Linganore High School]] {{convert|7|mi|0}} west of town, while Mount Airy students living in Carroll County attend [[South Carroll High School]] {{convert|10|mi|0}} northeast of town.\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Joe Alexander (basketball)|Joe Alexander]] (born 1986), American-Israeli professional basketball player for [[Maccabi Tel Aviv]]\n* [[Josh Boone (basketball)|Josh Boone]] (born 1984), NBA player\n* [[John M. Gaver, Sr.]], thoroughbred trainer in [[National Museum of Racing and Hall of Fame|Racing Hall of Fame]]\n* [[Rob Havenstein]] (born 1992), NFL player\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat|Mount Airy, Maryland}}\n* {{official website|http://www.mountairymd.org/}}\n\n{{Carroll County, Maryland}}\n{{Frederick County, Maryland}}\n{{DCMetroArea}}\n{{Geographic location\n| Center    = Mount Airy\n| North     = [[Westminster, Maryland|Westminster]]<br/>[[File:MD Route 27.svg|20px]] [[Maryland Route 27|MD 27 North]] \n| Northeast = [[Woodbine, Maryland|Woodbine]]<br/>Watersville Road\n| East      = [[Woodbine, Maryland|Woodbine]], [[Baltimore]]<br/>[[File:I-70.svg|20px]] [[Interstate 70 in Maryland|I-70 East]]\n| Southeast = [[Florence, Maryland|Florence]]<br/>Florence Road\n| Southwest = [[Green Valley, Maryland|Green Valley]]<br/>Penn Shop Road\n| South     = [[Damascus, Maryland|Damascus]]<br/>[[File:MD Route 27.svg|20px]] [[Maryland Route 27|MD 27 South]]\n| West      = [[New Market, Maryland|New Market]], [[Frederick, Maryland|Frederick]]<br/>[[File:I-70.svg|20px]] [[Interstate 70 in Maryland|I-70 West]]\n| Northwest = [[Libertytown, Maryland|Libertytown]]<br/>[[File:MD Route 75.svg|20px]] [[Maryland Route 75|MD 75 North]]\n}}\n[[Category:Towns in Carroll County, Maryland]]\n[[Category:Towns in Frederick County, Maryland]]\n", "name_user": "2601:14f:0:b86:8994:6f10:6f77:f1a4", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mount_Airy,_Maryland"}
